  "year": 2025,
  "abstract": "We present GRAPE (Group Representational Position Encoding), a unified framework for positional encoding based on group actions. GRAPE unifies two families of mechanisms: multiplicative rotations in SO(d) and additive logit biases arising from unipotent actions in the general linear group GL. Multiplicative GRAPE recovers RoPE as a special case and extends it through learned subspaces and compact non-commuting mixtures. Additive GRAPE recovers ALiBi and the Forgetting Transformer as special cases while preserving exact relative laws and streaming cacheability.",
